#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.121"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.121:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.121:0.2"
msgid "13. Bhayavagga"
msgstr "13. Fears"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: bhayasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.121:0.3"
msgid "121. Attānuvādasutta"
msgstr "121. Guilt"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.121:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, bhayāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four fears."

msgctxt "an4.121:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.121:1.3"
msgid "Attānuvādabhayaṃ, parānuvādabhayaṃ, daṇḍabhayaṃ, duggatibhayaṃ."
msgstr "The fears of guilt, shame, punishment, and going to a bad place."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.121:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, attānuvādabhayaṃ?"
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is the fear of guilt?"

msgctxt "an4.121:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "It’s when someone reflects:"

#. VAR: ahañceva → ahañce (?)
#. VAR: kiñca taṃ yaṃ maṃ → kiñca taṃ maṃ (bj) | kiñca maṃ (s1-3, km) | kiñca taṃ kammaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.121:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahañceva kho pana kāyena duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, vācāya duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, "
"manasā duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, kiñca taṃ yaṃ maṃ attā sīlato na upavadeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If I were to do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind, wouldn’t I "
"blame myself for my conduct?’"

msgctxt "an4.121:2.4"
msgid ""
"So attānuvādabhayassa bhīto kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, "
"vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya "
"manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati."
msgstr ""
"Being afraid of guilt, they give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and "
"mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping "
"themselves pure."

msgctxt "an4.121:2.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, attānuvādabhayaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the fear of guilt."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.122"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.121:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, parānuvādabhayaṃ?"
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is the fear of shame?"

msgctxt "an4.121:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "It’s when someone reflects:"

msgctxt "an4.121:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahañceva kho pana kāyena duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, vācāya duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, "
"manasā duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, kiñca taṃ yaṃ maṃ pare sīlato na upavadeyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If I were to do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind, wouldn’t "
"others blame me for my conduct?’"

msgctxt "an4.121:3.4"
msgid ""
"So parānuvādabhayassa bhīto kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, "
"vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya "
"manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati."
msgstr ""
"Being afraid of shame, they give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and "
"mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping "
"themselves pure."

msgctxt "an4.121:3.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, parānuvādabhayaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the fear of shame."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.121:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, daṇḍabhayaṃ?"
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is the fear of punishment?"

msgctxt "an4.121:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco passati coraṃ āgucāriṃ, rājāno gahetvā vividhā "
"kammakāraṇā kārente, "
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone sees that the kings have arrested a bandit, a criminal, "
"and subjected them to various punishments—"

msgctxt "an4.121:4.3"
msgid ""
"kasāhipi tāḷente, vettehipi tāḷente, addhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷente, hatthampi "
"chindante, pādampi chindante, hatthapādampi chindante, kaṇṇampi chindante, "
"nāsampi chindante, kaṇṇanāsampi chindante, bilaṅgathālikampi karonte, "
"saṅkhamuṇḍikampi karonte, rāhumukhampi karonte, jotimālikampi karonte, "
"hatthapajjotikampi karonte, erakavattikampi karonte, cīrakavāsikampi "
"karonte, eṇeyyakampi karonte, balisamaṃsikampi karonte, kahāpaṇakampi "
"karonte, khārāpatacchikampi karonte, palighaparivattikampi karonte, "
"palālapīṭhakampi karonte, tattenapi telena osiñcante, sunakhehipi "
"khādāpente, jīvantampi sūle uttāsente, asināpi sīsaṃ chindante."
msgstr ""
"whipping, caning, and clubbing; cutting off hands or feet, or both; cutting "
"off ears or nose, or both; the ‘porridge pot’, the ‘shell-shave’, the ‘demon’"
"s mouth’, the ‘garland of fire’, the ‘burning hand’, the ‘grass blades’, the "
"‘bark dress’, the ‘antelope’, the ‘meat hook’, the ‘coins’, the ‘acid pickle’"
", the ‘twisting bar’, the ‘straw mat’; being splashed with hot oil, being "
"fed to the dogs, being impaled alive, and being beheaded."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.121:5.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an4.121:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘yathārūpānaṃ kho pāpakānaṃ kammānaṃ hetu coraṃ āgucāriṃ rājāno gahetvā "
"vividhā kammakāraṇā kārenti, kasāhipi tāḷenti … pe … asināpi sīsaṃ "
"chindanti, ahañceva kho pana evarūpaṃ pāpakammaṃ kareyyaṃ, mampi rājāno "
"gahetvā evarūpā vividhā kammakāraṇā kāreyyuṃ, kasāhipi tāḷeyyuṃ, vettehipi "
"tāḷeyyuṃ, addhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷeyyuṃ, hatthampi chindeyyuṃ, pādampi "
"chindeyyuṃ, hatthapādampi chindeyyuṃ, kaṇṇampi chindeyyuṃ, nāsampi "
"chindeyyuṃ, kaṇṇanāsampi chindeyyuṃ, bilaṅgathālikampi kareyyuṃ, "
"saṅkhamuṇḍikampi kareyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘If I were to do the same kind of bad deed, the kings would punish me in the "
"same way.’ …"

msgctxt "an4.121:5.3"
msgid ""
"rāhumukhampi kareyyuṃ, jotimālikampi kareyyuṃ, hatthapajjotikampi kareyyuṃ, "
"erakavattikampi kareyyuṃ, cīrakavāsikampi kareyyuṃ, eṇeyyakampi kareyyuṃ, "
"balisamaṃsikampi kareyyuṃ, kahāpaṇakampi kareyyuṃ, khārāpatacchikampi "
"kareyyuṃ, palighaparivattikampi kareyyuṃ, palālapīṭhakampi kareyyuṃ, "
"tattenapi telena osiñceyyuṃ, sunakhehipi khādāpeyyuṃ, jīvantampi sūle "
"uttāseyyuṃ, asināpi sīsaṃ chindeyyun’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an4.121:5.4"
msgid "So daṇḍabhayassa bhīto na paresaṃ pābhataṃ vilumpanto carati."
msgstr "Being afraid of punishment, they don’t steal the belongings of others."

msgctxt "an4.121:5.5"
msgid "Kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya … pe … suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati."
msgstr ""
"They give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develop good "
"conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping themselves pure."

msgctxt "an4.121:5.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, daṇḍabhayaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the fear of punishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.123"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.121:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, duggatibhayaṃ?"
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is the fear of rebirth in a bad place?"

msgctxt "an4.121:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "It’s when someone reflects:"

msgctxt "an4.121:6.3"
msgid ""
"‘kāyaduccaritassa kho pāpako vipāko abhisamparāyaṃ, vacīduccaritassa pāpako "
"vipāko abhisamparāyaṃ, manoduccaritassa pāpako vipāko abhisamparāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Bad conduct of body, speech, or mind has a bad result in the next life."

msgctxt "an4.121:6.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana kāyena duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, vācāya duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, "
"manasā duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, kiñca taṃ yāhaṃ na kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"If I were to do such bad things, when my body breaks up, after death, I’d be "
"reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’"

msgctxt "an4.121:6.5"
msgid ""
"So duggatibhayassa bhīto kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, "
"vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya "
"manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati."
msgstr ""
"Being afraid of rebirth in a bad place, they give up bad conduct by way of "
"body, speech, and mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and "
"mind, keeping themselves pure."

msgctxt "an4.121:6.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, duggatibhayaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the fear of rebirth in a bad place."

msgctxt "an4.121:6.7"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayānī”ti."
msgstr "These are the four fears.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.121:6.8"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
